						               													<description>The Dauphin and the Sword is the 13th module in the series Au Fil de l'Ep&amp;eacute;e (By The Edge of the Sword) and First volume of &amp;quot;AFDE - Louis XI &amp;raquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It covers three battles of Louis XI, when he was still Dauphin of France (heir to the throne) and finally King of France: Dieppe (1443), Saint-Jacques-sur-la-Brise (1444) and Montlh&amp;eacute;ry (1465), which are, respectively, the 34th, 35th and 36th battles in the series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: Montlh&amp;eacute;ry is a new edition, much expanded, with new map, counters, and scenario specific rules of the battle published in 2007 with Ep&amp;#195;&amp;#169;es et Couronne (DTP).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes:&amp;#10;- 324 die-cut counters&amp;#10;- 2 A2 maps&amp;#10;- 1 A4 map&amp;#10;- One 16 pages booklet (rules, scenarios and historical notes&amp;#10;- One player aid&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Battles: &amp;#10;-  The Assault on the Fortress at Dieppe, August 14, 1443  (Louis, Dauphin of France vs. William Peyto, commander of English garrison of Dieppe)&amp;#10;- The Battle of Saint-Jacques-sur-la-Brise, August 26, 1444  (Louis, Dauphin of France &amp;amp; Jean de Bueil vs. Hans Matter, Swiss army leader)&amp;#10;- The Battle of Montlh&amp;eacute;ry, July 16, 1465 (Louis XI, King of France vs. Charles The Bold, Duke of Burgundy)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game features one historical scenario and one &amp;quot;what if?&amp;quot; scenario per battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cover and Rulebook in French OR English. Charts/Tables are bilingual (French/English).&amp;#10; Louis XI (of France) battles (1443-79):&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    The Dauphin and the Sword (Louis XI, vol. 1)&amp;#10;    The Truce or the Sword (Louis XI, vol. 2)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
